# Router Service Boundaries

For backend API changes, separate transport concerns from business logic by default.

## Layer responsibilities

- Routers (`backend/app/routers/**`) focus on endpoint wiring, parsing, auth dependencies, and HTTP mapping.
- Feature services (`backend/app/features/**/service.py`) own business rules, orchestration, sequencing, and non-trivial validation.
- Shared query helpers stay in feature modules (for example `queries.py`), not spread across routers.

## Extraction triggers

Move logic from router to service when:

- endpoint touches 2+ entities/tables in one workflow
- validation is conditional/cross-field/cross-entity
- endpoint performs upsert-or-create orchestration
- endpoint includes reusable naming/derivation logic
- endpoint contains repeated eager-load blocks or post-processing
